annotationA: DNA polymerase epsilon subunit; Participates in DNA repair and in chromosomal DNA replication
annotationB: Transcription factor B4; RNA polymerase II carboxy-terminal domain kinase activity; DNA-dependent ATPase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter; transcriptional open complex formation at RNA polymerase II promoter; nucleotide-excision repair; promoter clearance from RNA polymerase II promoter; regulation of transcription, DNA-templated; response to UV; transcription initiation from RNA polymerase II promoter
